The paper deals with embedding models for entities and relations in a knowledge base, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of an autoencoder for joint training, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on compositional constraints and knowledge base completion tasks suggests that it may also be relevant to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
